body:
https://nodejs.dev/en/api/v20/process/#when-to-use-queuemicrotask-vs-processnexttick or https://nodejs.org/docs/latest-v20.x/api/process.html#when-to-use-queuemicrotask-vs-processnexttick

```js
import { nextTick } from 'node:process';

Promise.resolve().then(() => console.log(2));
queueMicrotask(() => console.log(3));
nextTick(() => console.log(1));
// Output:
// 1
// 2
// 3
```

I ran this code locally, and its result was 2 3 1 instead of 1 2 3. Therefore, the statement "Within Node.js, every time the 'next tick queue' is drained, the microtask queue is drained immediately after" in the documentation may also be incorrect.

<img width="763" alt="image" src="https://github.com/nodejs/node/assets/58261676/88127ac6-a5c5-49b0-9fed-57e7846a19bb">

