body:
### What is the problem this feature will solve?

[`NODE_COMPILE_CACHE`](https://nodejs.org/docs/latest/api/cli.html#node_compile_cachedir) persists the V8 code cache when the process is terminating which means that if the script spawns itself then that child process wont benefit from the cache.

### What is the feature you are proposing to solve the problem?

Persist the V8 code cache before spawning a child process so it can benefit from the cache.

```js
import { execFileSync } from "child_process";

if (process.argv[2] === "foo") {
	console.log("foo");
} else {
	// Persist the V8 code cache
	console.log(execFileSync("node", ["test.mjs", "foo"]).toString());
}

```

### What alternatives have you considered?

_No response_

